Notices for graph-memory
========================

This project's graph schema, FalkorDB index definitions, and Cypher query
patterns are derived from graphiti (https://github.com/getzep/graphiti),
licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

Specifically, the range and fulltext index statements in
`pkg/gmem/client.go` are adapted from `graphiti_core/graph_queries.py`
(FalkorDB provider branch). The node/edge schema (Episodic, Entity,
Community, Saga; MENTIONS, RELATES_TO, HAS_MEMBER) and the temporal-fact
(invalidate + re-create) model follow graphiti's design.

Modifications relative to graphiti's source:
  - Reimplemented from Python to Go (no source code copied verbatim).
  - The FalkorDB range/fulltext index set is mirrored faithfully; edges not
    used by this project (e.g. graphiti's cross-provider bookkeeping edges
    when present) are simply not added.
  - group_id uses physical isolation (one FalkorDB graph per group).
  - Reasoning (entity extraction, invalidation judgment, summarization) is
    left to the calling agent rather than performed by an embedded LLM.
  - The extraction principles in `skills/graph-memory/references/extraction.md`
    are adapted from graphiti's LLM prompt files
    (`graphiti_core/prompts/extract_nodes.py`, `extract_edges.py`,
    `dedupe_nodes.py`, `dedupe_edges.py`, `summarize_nodes.py`,
    `summarize_sagas.py`), rewritten as agent-facing guidance.

